---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import ShitDoneCtaSection from '../components/ShitDoneCtaSection.astro';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="ACID Method | zomeren.studio"
  description="The ACID method: a holistic brand strategy framework using astrological elements as creative compass."
  lang="en"
  enPath="/acid-method/"
  nlPath="/nl/acid-methode/"
  schema={`{"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"WebPage","name":"ACID Method | zomeren.studio","description":"The ACID method: a holistic brand strategy framework using astrological elements as creative compass.","url":"https://zomeren.studio/acid-method/","inLanguage":"en-US","isPartOf":{"@type":"WebSite","name":"zomeren.studio","url":"https://zomeren.studio/"}}`}
>
  <Header enHref="/acid-method/" nlHref="/nl/acid-methode/" lang="en" />
  <main class="px-6 pb-24 pt-20 md:px-12 md:pb-36 md:pt-24">
    <section data-reveal class="py-10 md:py-16">
      <h1 class="fade-in-stagger m-0 text-[clamp(2.4rem,5vw,7rem)] leading-[1.08] tracking-[-0.022em]">
        The ACID Method<span style="font-size:0.6em; vertical-align:super;">&copy;</span> is a holistic approach that helps
        brands discover their true potential and express it fully.
      </h1>
    </section>

    <section data-reveal class="py-10 md:py-14">
      <div class="grid grid-cols-4 gap-8 lg:grid-cols-12">
        <div class="col-span-4 lg:col-span-3">
          <img src="/assets/images/marco/marco_van_zomeren_studio_4.webp" alt="Marco van Zomeren portrait"
            class="aspect-[2/3] w-full object-cover" loading="eager" decoding="async" />
        </div>

        <div class="hidden lg:block lg:col-span-3"></div>

        <div class="col-span-4 lg:col-span-6">
          <p class="text-[clamp(1.4rem,2vw,2.7rem)] leading-[1.24] tracking-[-0.012em]">
            It's an approach that starts with the human behind the brand and views everything through the lens of
            astrology: the air, water, earth, and fire archetypes. We can then translate insights into identity systems
            that feel naturally aligned.
          </p>
          <p class="mt-6 text-[clamp(1.4rem,2vw,2.7rem)] leading-[1.24] tracking-[-0.012em]">
            The ACID Method follows the natural synergy between the four astrological elements air, water, earth,
            and fire and uses them as thematic cues for the four phases of a brand's journey. Each element represents
            a unique energy that, together, shapes the complete story of a brand, from foundation to expression.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section data-reveal class="py-8 md:py-12">
      <div class="space-y-12 md:space-y-16">
        <article class="grid grid-cols-4 gap-8 border-b border-black/40 dark:border-white/40 pb-10 md:pb-12 lg:grid-cols-12">
          <div class="col-span-1 lg:col-span-2">
            <img src="/assets/svg/air.svg" alt="" class="h-20 w-20 object-contain brightness-0 dark:invert" aria-hidden="true" />
          </div>
          <div class="col-span-3 lg:col-span-8">
            <h2 class="text-[clamp(2.2rem,3.7vw,5rem)] leading-none tracking-[-0.02em]">A — Abstraction (Air)</h2>
            <p class="mt-3 text-[clamp(1.3rem,1.9vw,2.5rem)] leading-[1.2] tracking-[-0.01em]">Ideas, perception, conceptual framing</p>
            <p class="mt-4 text-[clamp(1.05rem,1.3vw,1.9rem)] leading-[1.3] tracking-[-0.01em] text-black/92 dark:text-white/92">
              Perception, cognition, and conceptual framing. In the design industry—spanning graphic, web, and digital design—the Air phase is about observation, analyzing patterns, and creating mental distance. We dissect the brand's core ideas, research user behaviors, and distill complex information into a high-level conceptual framework before any visual work begins.
            </p>
          </div>
        </article>

        <article class="grid grid-cols-4 gap-8 border-b border-black/40 dark:border-white/40 pb-10 md:pb-12 lg:grid-cols-12">
          <div class="col-span-1 lg:col-span-2">
            <img src="/assets/svg/water.svg" alt="" class="h-20 w-20 object-contain brightness-0 dark:invert" aria-hidden="true" />
          </div>
          <div class="col-span-3 lg:col-span-8">
            <h2 class="text-[clamp(2.2rem,3.7vw,5rem)] leading-none tracking-[-0.02em]">C — Connection (Water)</h2>
            <p class="mt-3 text-[clamp(1.3rem,1.9vw,2.5rem)] leading-[1.2] tracking-[-0.01em]">Emotion, empathy, relational flow</p>
            <p class="mt-4 text-[clamp(1.05rem,1.3vw,1.9rem)] leading-[1.3] tracking-[-0.01em] text-black/92 dark:text-white/92">
              Emotion, empathy, and relational flow. The Water phase is where we build the brand's emotional life and user empathy. In digital and graphic design, this translates to crafting intuitive user journeys, aligning aesthetic resonance with user needs, and ensuring the interface or identity communicates a genuine, human-centric story that naturally bonds the audience to the brand.
            </p>
          </div>
        </article>

        <article class="grid grid-cols-4 gap-8 border-b border-black/40 dark:border-white/40 pb-10 md:pb-12 lg:grid-cols-12">
          <div class="col-span-1 lg:col-span-2">
            <img src="/assets/svg/earth.svg" alt="" class="h-20 w-20 object-contain brightness-0 dark:invert" aria-hidden="true" />
          </div>
          <div class="col-span-3 lg:col-span-8">
            <h2 class="text-[clamp(2.2rem,3.7vw,5rem)] leading-none tracking-[-0.02em]">I — Intention (Earth)</h2>
            <p class="mt-3 text-[clamp(1.3rem,1.9vw,2.5rem)] leading-[1.2] tracking-[-0.01em]">Systems, structure, coherence</p>
            <p class="mt-4 text-[clamp(1.05rem,1.3vw,1.9rem)] leading-[1.3] tracking-[-0.01em] text-black/92 dark:text-white/92">
              Systems, structure, and coherence. The Earth phase grounds the vision by building solid design systems, structural grids, and technical architecture. For web and digital design, this is where we establish scalable layouts, UI components, typography hierarchies, and functional specifications to ensure consistency, durability, and a flawless user experience.
            </p>
          </div>
        </article>

        <article class="grid grid-cols-4 gap-8 border-b border-black/40 dark:border-white/40 pb-10 md:pb-12 lg:grid-cols-12">
          <div class="col-span-1 lg:col-span-2">
            <img src="/assets/svg/fire.svg" alt="" class="h-20 w-20 object-contain brightness-0 dark:invert" aria-hidden="true" />
          </div>
          <div class="col-span-3 lg:col-span-8">
            <h2 class="text-[clamp(2.2rem,3.7vw,5rem)] leading-none tracking-[-0.02em]">D — Disruption (Fire)</h2>
            <p class="mt-3 text-[clamp(1.3rem,1.9vw,2.5rem)] leading-[1.2] tracking-[-0.01em]">Action, change, breaking patterns</p>
            <p class="mt-4 text-[clamp(1.05rem,1.3vw,1.9rem)] leading-[1.3] tracking-[-0.01em] text-black/92 dark:text-white/92">
              Action, transformation, and breaking patterns. The Fire phase is about execution, dynamic motion, and bringing the creative work to life with bold, transformative energy. Through expressive graphic design, high-fidelity prototypes, micro-interactions, and launching the digital experience, we challenge the status quo and make a lasting impact in the market.
            </p>
          </div>
        </article>
      </div>
    </section>

    <ShitDoneCtaSection />
  </main>
  <Footer />
</BaseLayout>
